href="jms-00KI.xml"
addr="jms-00KI"
title="Closure of functions under identity and composition">identity function</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {id}_{A}\colon  A\to  A]]></fr:tex> is simply itself.</fr:p>
 <fr:p>Fix <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KR.xml"
addr="jms-00KR"
title="Bijection">bijections</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\to  C]]></fr:tex>, so that we have <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KR.xml"
addr="jms-00KR"
title="Bijection">inverses</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g^{-1}\colon  C\to  B]]></fr:tex>. The <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KR.xml"
addr="jms-00KR"
