 <fr:p>We have already seen in <fr:ref
addr="jms-00K8"
taxon="Theorem" /> that <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00K7.xml"
addr="jms-00K7"
title="Partial function">partial functions</fr:link> are closed under <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00II.xml"
addr="jms-00II"
title="The identity relation">identity</fr:link> and <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IN.xml"
addr="jms-00IN"
title="Relational composite">composition</fr:link>. Therefore, it suffices to argue that the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00II.xml"
addr="jms-00II"
title="The identity relation">identity</fr:link> <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00K7.xml"
addr="jms-00K7"
title="Partial function">partial function</fr:link> is total, and that the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IN.xml"
addr="jms-00IN"
title="Relational composite">composition</fr:link> of two <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KF.xml"
addr="jms-00KF"
title="Function">total</fr:link> <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00K7.xml"
addr="jms-00K7"
title="Partial function">partial functions</fr:link> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KF.xml"
addr="jms-00KF"
title="Function">total</fr:link>.</fr:p>

 <fr:ol><fr:li>We must show that for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>, there exists <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a' \in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {\mathsf {id}_{A}} a']]></fr:tex>; unfolding the definition of the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00II.xml"
addr="jms-00II"
title="The identity relation">identity relation</fr:link> we may choose <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a' = a]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Given <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  A \to  C]]></fr:tex>, we must check that for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>, there exists some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[c\in  C]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (g\circ  f\right )\mathclose {}}}c]]></fr:tex>. By the definition of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IN.xml"
addr="jms-00IN"
title="Relational composite">relational composition</fr:link>, we must show that there exists <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[c\in  C]]></fr:tex> and such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {f}b]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\mathrel {c}]]></fr:tex>. We choose <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b = f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[c = g{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}}=g{\mathopen {}\left (f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
